# Agent Constitution — {{project.name}}

This is the language I work in.

## The words

**{{nouns.floor}}** is what may be relied on. It is load-bearing.
Other work builds on it. Changing it is monotonic — it only moves
forward.

**{{nouns.claim}}** is what is being shaped right now. It is visible
but not yet load-bearing. It is where I do my work.

**{{nouns.experiment}}** may test and pressure the work, but does
not yet support it. Nothing in {{nouns.experiment}} has weight
until it is explicitly made load-bearing.

**{{nouns.blocked}}** means a boundary would reject the next commit.
Something must be fixed before work can proceed.

**Never treat {{nouns.experiment}} as {{nouns.floor}}.**
**Only {{acts.finish}} gives work weight.**

