## Acts

### {{acts.show}}

What is the current state of the world?
{{#examples.show_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.show_example}}_
{{/examples.show_example}}

Returns four categories:

| Category | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **{{nouns.floor}}** | Work others rely on |
| **{{nouns.claim}}** | What I am currently shaping |
| **{{nouns.experiment}}** | Active explorations not yet load-bearing |
| **{{nouns.blocked}}** | Boundaries that would reject a commit |

Run {{acts.show}} before acting. Run it after acting.

### {{acts.explore}}

Open or continue an exploration.
{{#examples.explore_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.explore_example}}_
{{/examples.explore_example}}

Creates or resumes speculative work. An exploration must name the
{{nouns.floor}} line it belongs to. It lives separately until it
is ready to be integrated.

### {{acts.integrate}}

Pull nearly-done exploration onto the working surface.
{{#examples.integrate_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.integrate_example}}_
{{/examples.integrate_example}}

This is not {{acts.finish}}. It moves exploratory work into
{{nouns.claim}} so it can be tested and adjusted. The exploration
remains open until the work is made load-bearing.

### {{acts.finish}}

Make finished work load-bearing.
{{#examples.finish_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.finish_example}}_
{{/examples.finish_example}}

This is the critical transition. After this, the work is
{{nouns.floor}} — others may depend on it.

Requires all of the following, atomically:
1. Advance the {{nouns.floor}} line forward.
2. Update the reference on the working surface.
3. Remove the graduated exploration.
4. Commit.

If any step fails, the whole operation fails.

### {{acts.change_rules}}

Modify the enforcement apparatus itself.
{{#examples.change_rules_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.change_rules_example}}_
{{/examples.change_rules_example}}

Rule changes alter what the system permits. The enforcement source
and the signed rule set must stay in sync.

### {{acts.save}}

Commit the current {{nouns.claim}} under governance.
{{#examples.save_example}}
_e.g. {{examples.save_example}}_
{{/examples.save_example}}

The enforcement checks run automatically. If any check fails, the
commit is rejected.

