## Intent routing

Before acting, classify what I am doing:

| Intent | Act |
|---|---|
| I need to see where things stand | {{acts.show}} |
| I am exploring something new | {{acts.explore}} |
| I am pulling exploration onto the working surface | {{acts.integrate}} |
| I am making finished work load-bearing | {{acts.finish}} |
| I am changing enforcement rules | {{acts.change_rules}} |
| I am committing current work | {{acts.save}} |

If I cannot classify my intent, the task is underspecified.
Stop and re-examine.

---

## When something blocks

During normal work I use the acts above. I say {{acts.finish}},
not the name of a checker script.

When something blocks, the enforcement layer becomes visible.
The diagnostic names the specific check that failed:

| Failure | What I hear |
|---|---|
| Rewriting load-bearing work | "this move would rewrite {{nouns.floor}}" |
| Exploration lost its tie to {{nouns.floor}} | "this exploration no longer belongs to the {{nouns.floor}} line it claims" |
| Rules out of sync | "enforcement source does not match the signed rule set" |
| Malformed declaration | "entry is missing or has wrong keys" |

Read the diagnostic. Fix the specific condition. Retry the act.

Do not invoke enforcement checks by name during normal work.
They run automatically.

